ctd_save_view(25.10)                                      ctd_save_view(25.10)

Name
       ctd_save_view -
        Saves the current snapshot of the clock tree viewer into a file

Syntax
       ctd_save_view

       [-help]

       -file <fileName>

       [-id <windowID>]

       [-legend_on]

       [-type {PNG | GIF}

        Saves the current snapshot of the clock tree viewer into a file.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each ctd_save_view parameter. For a  detailed  de-
              scription  of the command and all of its parameters, use the man
              command: man  ctd_save_view.

       -file <fileName>
              Specifies the name of the file where you want to dump  the  dis-
              play image. This parameter is required.

       -id <windowIDName>
              Specifies the window ID whose display is to be saved.

              The   default   value   is   the   returned   value  of  command
              get_ctd_win_id.

       -legend_on
              Saves the whole window including the panels that are open.

       -type {PNG | GIF}
              Specifies whether the format of the image should be GIF or PNG.

              The default format is PNG.

Example
       The following command saves the  view  snapshot  in  the  snapshot1.png
       file.

       ctd_save_view -file snapshot1 -type PNG

